<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>

<head>
    <title>Image Resizer Online</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2078364019879861"
        crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<body>
    {{>header}}
    <div class="container">
        <div class="main-content">
            <header style="text-align: center;">
                <h1>
                    Image Resizer Online
                </h1>
            </header>
            <form>
                <div class="control">
                    {{!-- <input type="file" id="upload"> --}}
                    <div class="file-input">
                        <input type="file" id="upload" class="file">
                        <label for="upload">
                            Select file
                        </label>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="control" style="padding: 0 0 0 10px;">
                    <p class="file-name"></p>
                </div>
                <div class="control">
                    <span style="margin-right: 50px">Width:</span><input id="width" type="number" value="100">
                </div>
                <div class="control">
                    <span style="margin-right: 45px">Height:</span> <input id="height" type="number" value="100">
                </div>
                <div class="control" id="controlBtns">
                    <button>Resize</button>
                </div>
            </form>

        </div>
        <script async
            src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2078364019879861"
            crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
        <!-- resize_1 -->
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-2078364019879861"
            data-ad-slot="6048845552" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
        <script>
            (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
        </script>
        <div class="image-container">
            <div class="input-output-container output-preview">
                <img id="output-image" />
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="image-compression-details">
            <script async
                src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2078364019879861"
                crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
            <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block; text-align:center;" data-ad-layout="in-article"
                data-ad-format="fluid" data-ad-client="ca-pub-2078364019879861" data-ad-slot="4718601950"></ins>
            <script>
                (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
            </script>
            <h3 class="detail-title">What is image resizing?</h3>
            <aside>
                Resizing is the process of changing the size of an image without cutting anything out. When you resize
                an image, you're just changing the file size. Because size does matter on occasion.
            </aside>
            <aside>
                Resizing your photo might make it fit into a specific area on a screen, such as a blog or social network
                post. Smaller photographs weigh less than larger ones, which might help speed up the uploading process
                or free up storage space on your devices.
            </aside>
        </div>
    </div>
    {{>footer}}
    <script src="/js/app.js"></script>
</body>

</html>